==English==
===Etymology===
From the Arabic {{ARchar|الرأس التنّين}} (''ar-ra’as at-tannīn'') ‘the dragon's head’, from {{ARchar|[[رأس]]}} ‘head’ + {{ARchar|[[تنين]]}} ‘dragon’.

===Noun===
'''Eltanin'''
# an orange giant [[star]], the brightest in the [[constellation]] of [[Draco]]

